msgid "After **Jamestown’s** founding, English colonization of the New World accelerated. In 1609, a ship bound for Jamestown foundered in a storm and landed on Bermuda. (Some believe this incident helped inspire Shakespeare’s 1611 play *The Tempest*.) The admiral of the ship, George Somers, claimed the island for the English crown. The English also began to colonize small islands in the Caribbean, an incursion into the Spanish American empire. They established themselves on small islands such as St. Christopher in 1624, Barbados in 1627, Nevis in 1628, Montserrat in 1632, and Antigua in 1632."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-2/apush-early-english-settlement/a/intro-to-english-settlement">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-2/apush-early-english-settlement/a/intro-to-english-settlement</a>.
