# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "By any measure, England came late to the race to colonize. As Jamestown limped along in the 1610s, the Spanish Empire extended around the globe and grew rich from its global colonial project. Yet the English persisted, and for this reason the [Jamestown](/humanities/us-history/colonial-america/early-english-settlement/v/early-english-settlements-jamestown) settlement has a special place in history as the first permanent colony in what later became the United States."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-2/apush-early-english-settlement/a/intro-to-english-settlement">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-2/apush-early-english-settlement/a/intro-to-english-settlement</a>.
