# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: pt)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "In 1630, a much larger contingent of Puritans left England to escape conformity to the Church of England and founded the [Massachusetts Bay Colony](/humanities/ap-us-history/period-2/apush-colonial-north-america/a/puritan-new-england-massachusetts-bay). In the following years, thousands more arrived to create a new life in the rocky soils and cold climates of New England."
msgstr ""

