msgid "Fast forward to August. Jim takes all of the cotton he and his family has grown to the market, where he discovers that cotton prices have fallen to \\$2 per bale. So when Jim sells all of his cotton, he only makes \\$200. Not only did Jim not profit on his year of farming cotton, he can't pay back his loan to Samuel, and still owes him \\$100. Since he's in debt to Samuel, Jim can't just leave the farm; he has to find a way to pay Samuel back. The only thing Jim has to sell is his labor, growing cotton on Samuel's land. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-6/apush-south-after-civil-war/a/the-new-south">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-6/apush-south-after-civil-war/a/the-new-south</a>.
