msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* In **Korematsu v. United States** (1944) the Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of internment. In 1988, the United States issued an official apology for internment and compensated survivors."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* Japanese Americans sold their businesses and houses for a fraction of their value before being sent to the camps. In the process, they lost their livelihoods and much of their lifesavings.  "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* President Franklin Roosevelt’s Executive Order 9066 resulted in the relocation of 112,000 Japanese Americans living on the West Coast into **internment camps** during the Second World War.   "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "In 1984, a federal court voided Korematsu’s conviction, and in 1998 President [Bill Clinton](/humanities/us-history/modern-us/1990s-america/a/bill-clinton-as-president) bestowed the Presidential Medal of Freedom, the nation’s highest civilian honor, on Fred Korematsu.$^6$"
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/japanese-internment</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "In February 1942, President [Franklin Roosevelt](/humanities/us-history/rise-to-world-power/us-wwii/a/fdr-and-world-war-ii) issued **Executive Order 9066**, which authorized the Secretary of War to declare certain areas within the United State as military zones, and to restrict access to those areas on the grounds of wartime military necessity.  The president’s order came less than three months after Japan’s attack on [Pearl Harbor](/humanities/us-history/rise-to-world-power/us-wwii/a/pearl-harbor), amid concerns that Japanese American citizens might pose a threat to national security. These concerns were driven by public hysteria grounded in racism and false reports of sabotage and collaboration with the enemy. "
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/pearl-harbor">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/pearl-harbor</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* Across the nation, Americans were stunned, shocked, and angered. The attack turned US public opinion in favor of entering the **Second World War**. The United States declared war on Japan on December 8, 1941."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/the-manhattan-project-and-the-atomic-bomb">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-7/apush-us-wwii/a/the-manhattan-project-and-the-atomic-bomb</a>.
