#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "Rock and roll music celebrated themes such as young love and freedom from the oppression of middle-class society. It quickly grew in favor among American teens during the 1950s, thanks largely to the efforts of disc jockey Alan Freed. Freed named and popularized rock and roll by playing it on the radio in Cleveland—where he also organized the first rock and roll concert—and later in New York."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-1950s-america/a/popular-culture-and-mass-media-cnx">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-1950s-america/a/popular-culture-and-mass-media-cnx</a>.
