# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: es)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "The theme of rebellion against authority, present in many rock and roll songs, appealed to teens. In 1954, rock group Bill Haley and His Comets provided youth with an anthem for their rebellion with the song ”Rock Around the Clock.” The song, used in the 1955 movie *Blackboard Jungle* about a white teacher at a troubled inner-city high school, seemed to be calling for teens to declare their independence from adult control."
msgstr ""

