# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* The experiences of African American soldiers during World War II inspired many of them to agitate for civil rights when they returned to civilian life. Even though black soldiers faced discrimination from within the American military, they had the opportunity to observe societies where **Jim Crow** racism was not the law of the land."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* **Malcolm X** was the most influential thinker of what became known as the Black Power movement, and inspired others like **Stokely Carmichael** of the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee and **Huey P. Newton** and **Bobby Seale** of the Black Panther Party."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "* **“Black Power”** refers to a militant ideology that aimed not at integration and accommodation with white America, but rather preached black self-reliance, self-defense, and racial pride."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power">http://translate.khanacademy.org/humanities/ap-us-history/period-8/apush-civil-rights-movement/a/black-power</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: de)
